Class StringInterpretation<Constant,Concept,Attribute,DataType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractObjects.StringInterpretation<Constant,Concept,Attribute,DataType>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Interpretation<java.lang.String,Constant,java.lang.String,Concept,java.lang.String,Attribute,java.lang.String,DataType>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Context

    public class StringInterpretation<Constant,Concept,Attribute,DataType>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Interpretation<java.lang.String,Constant,java.lang.String,Concept,java.lang.String,Attribute,java.lang.String,DataType>
    This class allows one to map Strings/Identifiers to Constants, Concepts and Attributes and DataTypes. The insertion and removal of constants, concepts and attributes can be watched by observers. An observer is a BiConsumer with the objects as first argument and true/false as second argument. true means insertion, false means removal.
